The image distance $b$ can be adjusted by a retractable bellows, and the object distance $g$ can be adjusted by a rotatable MOF as can be seen in Fig.~\ref{fig1}. The large background of low-energy delta electrons ($\delta$) are suppressed by selecting an optimized transmission. This filter also deflects the positive beta electrons ($\beta^+$) to the outer side of the detector.



